         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">1/6/88 ¶  ¶ Today, noble Friend, I am sending you some algae just arrived from Israelite Bay ¶  that Miss Brook ¶ s ¶  (not Brook ¶ e ¶  as I wrote previously from her indistinct signature) ¶  sent me...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">88.06.01a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Jacob Agardh</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Handskr. <seg style="">Avdl., Universitetsbibliotek, Lund, Sweden.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">1/6/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Heute, edler Freund, sende ich Ihnen einige eben angelangte Algen von der Israelite-Bai, welche Miss Brook</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">s</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> (nicht Brook</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">e</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">, wie ich früher nach deren undeutlicher Unterschrift schrieb) mir sendet. Es sind für mich einige ganz neue Formen dabei; ich sende Ihnen aber auch Dasyphila u andere gewöhnliche Arten, da der Standort noch dafür neu sein mag. Die </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Localität</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> ist überdies sehr </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">bemerkenswerth</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">, denn am westlichen Ende der "Great Bight" </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">begegnen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> sich nicht nur die östlichen u westlichen Phanerogamen, sondern wohl auch in so fern die Algen. Stets Sie ehrend</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">Einige </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">baldige</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Notizen würden diese junge geistreiche Dame gewiss zum Weitersammeln an der reichen Fundstelle bald weiter ermuntern.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1/6/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Today, noble Friend, I am sending you some algae just arrived from Israelite Bay<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>WA.</p>
               </note> that Miss Brook<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">s</hi>
               </seg> (not Brook<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">e</hi>
               </seg> as I wrote previously from her indistinct signature)<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Agardh, 15 June 1885 (in this edition as 85-06-15a). </p>
               </note> sent me. There are some forms quite new for me among them: but I am sending you even <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Dasyphila</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Dasyphylla</seg>?</p>
               </note> and other common species, because the locality may still be new for them. The <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">locality</hi>
               </seg> is moreover very <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">remarkable</hi>
               </seg>, since at the western end of the "Great Bight"<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Great Australian Bight.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> not only the eastern and western phanerogams <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">meet</hi>
               </seg>, but probably also in so far as the algae. Always honouring you</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Some <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">early</hi>
               </seg> notes would certainly soon further encourage this young intelligent woman to continue collecting at the rich place.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dasyphilia">Dasyphilia</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
